<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="486" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[783,1376,599,1023]" pageId="5" pageNumber="486">This species has often been classified as a subspecies of A. ursinus, but it is better recognized as a distinct species. No subspecies are recognized, but studies of distinctions between geographically isolated populations in central and south-western Sulawesi are needed. Monotypic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
